      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:133:1",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) إِنَّ أَعْجَلَ الشَّرِّ عُقُوبَةً الْبَغْيُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Ja’far Bin Muhammad Al Ashary, from Ibn Qaddah, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘The quickest of the Punishment of the evil, is for the transgression’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. A number of our people have narrated from Sahl ibn Ziyad from Ja’far ibn Muhammad al-Ash’ari from ibn al-Qaddah from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “The Messenger of Allah has said, ‘The evil most quickly facing punishment is tyrannical transgression.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
